---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Async AI Inference API Demo - Ahmad Saladin"
  description="Placeholder PoC page for an async AI inference API flow with job submission, queue workers, storage, status checks, and callbacks."
  sideBarActiveItemID="pocs"
>
  <article class="prose max-w-3xl">
    <p class="not-prose text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-primary">Guided demo planned</p>
    <h1>Async AI Inference API Demo</h1>
    <h2>What It Does</h2>
    <p>This PoC will simulate a long-running AI inference workflow: submit job, queue, process, store result, check status, and receive callback.</p>
    <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
    <p>Teams building model-serving APIs, image processing systems, batch inference, or AI backends.</p>
    <h2>Demo Status</h2>
    <p>For v0, this is a placeholder or static walkthrough. It is not a live backend demo yet.</p>
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <p>User -> Frontend -> API -> Queue -> Worker -> Storage -> Status / Callback</p>
    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>FastAPI, queue workers, Redis, RabbitMQ, object storage, Docker, webhooks.</p>
    <h2>Limitations</h2>
    <p>The v0 version does not submit real jobs, run workers, store generated outputs, or depend on any hosted queue/API service.</p>
    <h2>Productionization Plan</h2>
    <p>Production work would add auth, monitoring, retries, error handling, rate limits, job evaluation, scaling, and cost controls.</p>
    <h2>CTA</h2>
    <p>Want to build something like this? <a href="/contact">Contact me</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
